# Deployment Checklist

See [DEPLOY.md](../../DEPLOY.md) for the full cold-deploy and post-deploy verification checklist. Release train: [ROADMAP.md](../../ROADMAP.md) deploy gate (v1.8.1 tag after device QA).

## Environment (root `.env`)

All services read a **single repo root** `.env` (see [.env.example](../../.env.example)). Optional sync: `scripts/setup-env.ps1` or `scripts/setup-env.sh`.

## 1. Supabase

1. Create project at supabase.com
2. Run `supabase/migrations/001_initial_schema.sql`
3. Copy URL + service role key

## 2. Railway — API

1. New service from `packages/api/` (Dockerfile)
2. Set env: `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`, `TELEGRAM_WEBAPP_SECRET`, `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`
3. Verify `GET /health` returns `{"status":"ok"}`

## 3. Vercel — Mini App

1. Import repo, root directory `apps/mini-app`
2. Set env: `VITE_API_URL` (Railway API URL), `VITE_BOT_USERNAME`, `VITE_PROMPT_ANATOMY_URL` (optional; defaults in code)
3. Deploy, copy production URL

## 4. Railway — Bot

1. New service from `apps/bot/` (Dockerfile)
2. Set env: `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`, `MINI_APP_URL` (Vercel URL)

## 5. BotFather

1. `/setdomain` — set Vercel domain
2. Bot Settings → Menu Button → Configure Mini App URL
3. Test `/start` in Telegram

## 6. Preflight & smoke

From repo root:

```powershell
.\scripts\verify-deploy-config.ps1
.\scripts\smoke-local.ps1
```

Smoke runs: API `pytest`, bot import, mini-app `lint` + `test` + `build` + viewport QA, deploy preflight.

## 7. Post-deploy smoke

- Open Mini App from bot
- Play one run, verify score on Daily leaderboard
- Test share button
- v1.6: milestone chip, death cause row, retry tip visible on game over
